properties.description:
Signs of an emergency may include:

• Active suicidal/homicidal feelings

• Chest pain or heart attack symptoms 

• Significant difficulty breathing

• Stroke symptoms (facial drooping, arm weakness, speech difficulty)

• Severe allergic reaction

• Fever greater than 104.5°F

• Coughing or vomiting blood

• Sudden, severe, uncontrolled pain

• Severe headache

• Loss of consciousness/changes in mental status

• Poisoning/inhalation of substances

• Moderate to severe wounds/burns

• Seizures

• Significant trauma/head injury

• Pregnancy complications (vaginal bleeding, cramping, or abdominal pain)

fields.title: If you are experiencing a medical emergency, please call 911 or seek immediate medical attention.

properties.description:
If you’re experiencing any of the following, we recommend canceling this intake and scheduling a primary care visit.

• New or rapidly worsening pain, especially if accompanied by fever, night sweats, nausea, or vomiting

• Unexplained weight loss or gain

• Pain worsening at night, especially in bones or joints

• Morning back stiffness lasting more than 60 minutes

• Pain or symptoms related to previous cancer history or treatment

• Vertigo or other inner ear dysfunction

properties.description:
We recommend a PT consultation to identify the best next steps. During the consultation one of our licensed physical therapists will:

• Evaluate if Nice’s virtual physical therapy model will meet your needs.

• Share resources and information about your condition.

• If needed, provide guidance for finding an in-person physical therapist and answer questions about what to expect.
